76561198004427691,Recommended,322850,16555837,"Posted: 20 June, 2015",all,whitesoxs01,"I have played almsot every pro cycling game for the last 8 years. I really like the 1st player career mode, only a few weeks into the season but it is a great addition to a game that over the last few years hasn't added much. Which is why typically I don't suggest buying the new game until it has been out a while. As always with a new game it will crash occastionally and I'm sure they will put out patches soon as the game as only been out 2 days now.1st person career mode:You determine what type of cyclist you want to be (sprinter, climber, stage races, et cetera).Then pick your team, typically a contentional or contentional pro team.You have a race director or tell you want he would like you do during the race (just like in old career modes you used to give to your riders). So he declares you the leader, or free element, or teammate, and gives specific instructions like don't attack, ride in the breakaway, follow counter attacks, et cetera.You have a small number of points that you are allowed to use to adjust your race schedule during the year, which is nice when you want to get more training in.You select how much workload for your training, which in effect hurts your freshness for when races come up, so you need to decide how many rest days you want.Overall just a great addition, and as always if you like the career mode as a manager that has changed a little, they do R&D now on equipment, but quickly other than that I didn't see any major changes from previous version of the game.So far I highly recommend this game if you like cycling. I will update if any major issues arise."
